catalogue
data/ contains processed differential-expression results and other data tables used in the downstream analyses.
fig1/ contains the final output and related source material for Figure 1.
fig2/ contains the final output and related source material for Figure 2.
script/ contains the main R scripts used for statistical analysis and figure generation:
01_gene_dotplot.R: marker-gene dot-plot analysis and visualization;
02_cell_proportion_analysis.R: comparison of immune-cell proportions between study groups;
03_cell_cell_interaction.R: cell–cell communication analysis and visualization;
04_tcr_repertoire_analysis.R: T-cell receptor repertoire and clonotype analysis;
05_bcr_repertoire_analysis.R: B-cell receptor repertoire and clonotype analysis;
06_pseudotime_trajectory.R: pseudotime and branch-dependent transcriptional analysis;
07_transcription_factor_analysis.R: transcription-factor regulon activity analysis and visualization.
supporting information/ contains the source document for the supplementary figures and their legends.
table/ contains the supplementary tables associated with the manuscript.

Usage
Clone or download this repository:
git clone https://github.com/guoy8269-lgtm/ScRNA-Seq-Profiling-Acute-Phase-Immune-in-Human-Scrub-Typhus.git
Open the required R script in R or RStudio.
Install the R packages specified in each script.
Modify local input and output paths where necessary.
Run the scripts according to the analysis of interest.
The scripts were developed for the analyses reported in the manuscript. Users may need to adjust file paths, object names, factor levels, and package versions before applying them in a different computing environment.

Data availability
This repository contains processed data tables, analysis scripts, and figure-related files. Raw sequencing data and potentially identifiable clinical information are not included.
The accession number and repository information for the raw sequencing data will be provided in the manuscript or added here after public release.

Citation
If you use the data, scripts, or analytical workflow provided in this repository, please cite the corresponding paper:
Guo Y, et al. Single-cell profiling of acute-phase immune responses in human scrub typhus. iMeta. 2026.
Before formal publication, please cite this GitHub repository:
Guo Y. ScRNA-Seq Profiling of Acute-Phase Immune Responses in Human Scrub Typhus. GitHub repository.
https://github.com/guoy8269-lgtm/ScRNA-Seq-Profiling-Acute-Phase-Immune-in-Human-Scrub-Typhus
